<p><b>Irving Kristol</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1920-01-22"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-22"><a href="/wiki/January_22" title="January 22">January 22</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1920" title="1920">1920</a></span>) has been dubbed the "godfather of <a href="/wiki/Neoconservatism_(United_States)" title="Neoconservatism (United States)" class="mw-redirect">neoconservatism</a>."<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> As the founder, editor, and contributor to various magazines, he has played an influential role in the intellectual and political culture of the last half-century.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
